David Adeleke, popularly known as Davido, has signed singer, Akinmayokun ‘May D’ Awodumila, to his record label DMW. May D took to his official Twitter page on Saturday morning announcing his new label. The ‘soundtrack’ crooner expressed his excitement to join DMW. His tweet reads: “My new family, I’m so excited! DMW! DAILY POST recalls that May D had accused P-Square and Jude Okoye, owner of Northside Entertainment, of treating him poorly while he was under their management. May D had in a series of tweets revealed he had no personal bank account despite releasing hit songs and claimed he shared the boys quarter in the Okoye’s home with their cook and slept on carton.